main event: A witness observed 5 bright, oblong-shaped, yellow objects proceeding in formation through the sky at a high rate of speed (estimated 600-700 mph) over Ashland, Wisconsin on July 11, 1962.
interesting points: The witness estimated the objects were traveling at approximately 600-700 mph.
The witness felt the phenomena was unexplainable, as there were no known aircraft or astronomical objects in the area at the time.
The witness considered the possibility of flashing lights reflecting off clouds, but still felt the sighting was unexplainable.
The Air Force requested the witness complete a detailed technical information sheet to provide more information about the observation.
